<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Type: system_and_version_identification_item 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.system_and_version_identification_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.system_and_version_identification_item">
System_and_version_identification_item extends the identification_item select to allow alias identification asssignments to system and system_version entities
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Type: System_classified_select 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System_classified_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.system_classified_select">
System_classified_select extends the classified_select type to allow classification of system entities
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Type: system_organization_or_person_in_organization_item 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.system_organization_or_person_in_organization_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.system_organization_or_person_in_organization_item">
system_organization_or_person_in_organization_item extends the organization_or_person_in_organization_item type to allow persons or organizations to be assigned to systems, versions of systems, system version associations and system classifications.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: Class_of_system  
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.Class_of_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.Class_of_system">
The Class_of_system entity is a specialization of the general class entity - it is used to define classes of systems.
<example>
Typical classes of system could be "environment", "power source", "vehicle", "spacecraft" etc.
</example>
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: Classification_of_system  
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system">
The Classification_of_system entity is a specialization of the general classification entity - it is used to classify systems by relating system entities to class_of_system entities.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: Classification_of_system  Attribute: classified 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system.classified"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system.classified">
Relates to a system that is classified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: Classification_of_system  Attribute: classifier 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system.classifier"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.Classification_of_system.classifier">
Relates to a class which classifies a system.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: System  
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.System">
The System entity is used to identify systems.
<note number="1">
A system is any thing - matter, energy, or information or a combination of these - for which reproducible measurements exist. The concept system excludes any asserted thing based on personal experience for which no reproducible measurements exist.
</note>
<note number="2">
SEDRES Definition: "An assembly of interacting, active components or elements forming a whole".
</note>
<note number="3">
Another definition would be "That which is discernable by reproducable measurement of its characteristics, and has a defined boundary (statically and dynamically) with respect to the universe". Systems engineering tools and organizations may use differing identification mechanisms. Multiple identifiers may be assigned to a requirement using the Alias_identifier entity.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: System_version  
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version">
The System_version entity represents a version of a system. 
<note number="1">
In this case, this means "revision". So for a given system (e.g. a fuel injection system) we may have several versions of the system design (e.g. v1, v1.1 etc.)
</note>
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: System_version_sequence  
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence">
        The System_version_sequence entity is used to relate a previous version of a system to the version that replaces it.
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: System_version_sequence  Attribute: predecessor 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence.predecessor"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence.predecessor">
Relates to the previous system_version
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: System_identification_and_version_arm  Entity: System_version_sequence  Attribute: succecessor 
   <express_ref linkend="system_identification_and_version:arm:System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence.succecessor"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="System_identification_and_version_arm.System_version_sequence.succecessor">
Relates to the succeeding system_version
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
